      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here are 5 street-level characters that can add authenticity to your noir detective novel:\n\n1. Sal \"The Bull\" Martinez - a Mexican-American loan shark with a penchant for cigars and a soft spot for those in need. He's a wheeler-dealer with a network of underworld connections, but he's also a master manipulator who'll screw you over if it suits him.\n2. Fatima \"Fatty\" Hassan - a Middle Eastern-American street vendor who runs a food cart out of a crumbling alleyway, serving up spicy falafel to the locals who are too lazy to cook for themselves. She's always gossiping and spreading rumors, and she's got a mouth on her that could get her into trouble.\n3. Vinny \"The Knife\" LaRosa - an Italian-American small-time crook and enforcer for a local crime family, with a razor-sharp temper and a love for classic rockabilly music. He's a real piece of work, always looking for an excuse to pick a fight.\n4. Boots \"The Kid\" Jackson - a rough-around-the-edges African American street rat with a knack for fixing broken appliances and getting into trouble. He's always talking trash and causing a scene,",
